Imo State male football team Coach, Johnny Anyagwa, believes his team has the qualities needed to win the gold medal in the event at the ongoing National Sports Festival in Benin City, Edo State.
 
Imo State thrashed Delta State 4-2 in their opening match of the event on Wednesday at the University of Benin Sports Complex Mainbowl.
Speaking to The Guardian at the end of the match, an elated Anyagwa said he was certain his boys would cart home the gold medal, adding, “Judging from what I just saw in the match, I am certain that my boys are ready for this competition. We started grooming these boys even before the COVID-19 pandemic last year.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .